T1  - The cyclical behavior of prices and quantities: The case of the automobile market
AU  - Blanchard, Olivier J.
AU  - Melino, Angelo
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 17
IS  - 3
SP  - 379
EP  - 407
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/05/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(86)90064-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393286900644
AB  - This paper aims at understanding the joint behavior of prices and quantities in a particular market. It examines whether we can find decision problems for suppliers and buyers, together with a market structure, which are consistent with observed price and quantity series. Because of the homogeneity of the product and the quality of the data, we study the automobile market. We conclude that the behavior of prices is inconsistent with simple market structures. Prices appear to be too ‘sticky’. We then consider potential explanations. None appears completely satisfactory. In particular, costs of changing prices do not explain the joint behavior of prices and quantities.
ER  - 

