T1  - The effects of a shift in monetary policy regime on the profitability and risk of commercial banks
AU  - Aharony, Joseph
AU  - Saunders, Anthony
AU  - Swary, Ithzak
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 17
IS  - 3
SP  - 363
EP  - 377
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/05/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(86)90063-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393286900632
AB  - This paper examines the effects of the Fed's October 6th, 1979 change in monetary policy regime on the profitability and risk of commercial banks. Using capital market data and an event study methodology it was found that bank stocks exhibited significant abnormal returns during the announcement week of the policy change. When these abnormal returns were decomposed into a part related to unexpected interest rate changes and a part (assumed) to reflect increased rate variability, the results were consistent with a negative relationship between bank returns and interest rate surprises as well as between bank returns and rate variability.
ER  - 

