AB  - It is widely recognized that simple perfect foresight maximizing models often allow a continuum of hyperinflationary equilibria in the presence of a fixed money supply. Various attempts have been made to restrict the number of equilibria in such models. This paper illustrates some new aspects of a recent proposal.
